The paper deals with person re-identification using deep learning methods, specifically Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves learning hash functions for efficient matching, which could fall under machine learning (cs.MM) and learning theory (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization techniques for convergence and stability, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
